data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
1. Rental Agreement By signing this rental agreement, the renter agrees to rent a vehicle from Rent 'n Roll under the following terms and conditions.
2. Eligibility Age Requirement: Renter must be at least 21 years old. Driver’s License: Renter must possess a valid driver’s license that has been held for at least one year. Payment: Renter must provide a valid credit or debit card for payment and deposit.
3. Rental Period Start and End Dates: The rental period shall commence on the date and time specified in the rental agreement and shall end on the date and time specified. Extensions: Any request to extend the rental period must be approved by the Company and may incur additional charges.
4. Vehicle Use Authorized Drivers: Only the Renter and any additional drivers listed in the agreement are authorized to drive the vehicle.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
5. Insurance and Liability Insurance: The vehicle is covered by the Company's insurance policy. Renter is responsible for any deductible in case of a claim. Additional Insurance: Renter may opt to purchase additional insurance coverage. Damage and Loss: Renter is liable for any damage to or loss of the vehicle during the rental period. This includes, but is not limited to, theft, collision, and any interior or exterior damage. Accidents: In the event of an accident, Renter must report it immediately to the Company and follow the procedure outlined in the rental agreement.
6. Mileage Policy Unlimited Mileage: Rentals include unlimited mileage unless otherwise specified. Mileage Limit: If a mileage limit is specified, any excess mileage will be charged at the rate outlined in the rental agreement.
7. Return Policy Condition of Vehicle: The vehicle must be returned in the same condition as at the start of the rental period, barring normal wear and tear. Late Returns: Late returns may incur additional charges as outlined in the rental agreement. Early Returns: No refunds will be given for early returns.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
8. Cancellations and Modifications Cancellations: Cancellations must be made at least 24 hours before the rental start time to avoid a cancellation fee. Modifications: Any modifications to the rental agreement must be approved by the Company and may incur additional charges.
9. Privacy Policy Personal Information: The Company will collect and use personal information in accordance with its privacy policy, which is available on the Company’s website. Data Protection: The Company will take reasonable measures to protect personal information from unauthorized access or disclosure.
10. Governing Law This rental agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the state in which the rental is made.
11. Agreement Acceptance By signing below, the Renter acknowledges that they have read, understood, and agree to the terms and conditions of this rental agreement.
